    <br />
    <div class="maindiv">
        <h3>Live Attenuated Vaccines</h3>
        <p>Live attenuated vaccines use alive but weakened bacteria or viruses, which can still function and generate an immune response without causing the disease. This still requires the person to have a functional immune system, otherwise it can cause an infection when the weakened germs multiply. This type of vaccine is common and includes the chickenpox, mumps, measles, rubella and BCG vaccines.</p>
        <br />
    </div>
